1857  c = ref_kbmcmerv(dp->cms, rank_bitvec(dp->cmask, x + y * aux->qnbit));
1858  for(i=0;i<c->kcnt;i++){
1859  sidx = seed2solid_idx_kbm(aux->kbm, dp->kms->buffer + c->koff + i);
1860  one_bitvec(aux->solids, sidx); // Thread-unsafe, but no hurt
1861  }
1862  } else {
1863  }
1864  switch(bt){
1865  case 0: x --; y --; break;
1866  case 1: x --; break;
1867  default: y --; break;
1868  }
1869  }
1870  }
1871  hit->qe = (hit->qe + 1);
1872  hit->tb = (dp->boff + hit->tb - aux->kbm->reads->buffer[hit->tidx].binoff);
1873  hit->te = (dp->boff + hit->te - aux->kbm->reads->buffer[hit->tidx].binoff + 1);
1874  hit->mat = mat;
1875  hit->cnt = cnt;
1876  hit->gap = gap;
1877  hit->cgoff = cgoff;
1878  hit->cglen = cglen;
1879  //if(hit->qe > (int)aux->qlen) hit->qe = aux->qlen;
1880  //if(hit->te > (int)aux->kbm->reads->buffer[hit->tidx].rdlen) hit->te = aux->kbm->reads->buffer[hit->tidx].rdlen;
1881  if(dir){
1882  tmp = aux->qnbin - hit->qb;
1883  hit->qb = aux->qnbin - hit->qe;
1884  hit->qe = tmp;
1885  }
1886 #if __DEBUG__
1887  if(KBM_LOG){
1888  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "HIT\tQ[%d]\t%c\t%d\t%d", hit->qidx, "+-"[hit->qdir], hit->qb, hit->qe);
1889  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\tT[%d]\t%c\t%d\t%d", hit->tidx, "+-"[hit->tdir], hit->tb, hit->te);
1890  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\t%d\t%d\t%d\t%d\n", hit->mat, hit->aln, hit->cnt, hit->gap);
1891  }
1892 #endif
1893  return 1;
1894 }

1687  masks[1]->bits[i >> 6] = masks[0]->bits[i >> 6] | dp->cmask->bits[(i + bitoff) >> 6];
1688  }
1689  // dp core
1690  H = KBM_CELL_NULL;
1691  i = next_one_bitvec(masks[1], 0);
1692  D = (i && get_bitvec(masks[0], i - 1))? cells[0]->buffer[i - 1] : KBM_CELL_NULL;
1693  reg_zeros_bitvec(masks[0], 0, i);
1694  encap_bit2vec(dp->bts, aux->qnbin);
1695  n = 0;
1696  while(i < aux->qnbin){
1697  if(get_bitvec(dp->cmask, i + bitoff)){
1698  is_gap = 0;
1699  m = ref_kbmcmerv(dp->cms, rowoff + n);
1700  score = m->kmat + m->kcnt;
1701  n ++;
1702  } else {
1703  is_gap = 1;
1704  m = (kbm_cmer_t*)&KBM_CMER_NULL;
1705  score = aux->par->pgap;
1706  }
1707  // horizontal
1708  {
1709  H.score += score;
1710  H.mat += m->kmat;
1711  //H.gap = 0;
1712  }
1713  if(H.var < 0){
1714  H.score += - aux->par->pvar; // score increases for abs(var) decreased
1715  } else {
1716  H.score += aux->par->pvar;
1717  }
1718  H.var ++;
1719  H.bt = 1; // horizontal backtrace, insertion for query sequence
1720  // diagonal
1721  {
1722  D.score += score;
1723  D.mat += m->kmat;
1724  //D.gap = 0;
1725  }
1726  D.var = 0; // whether to reset var
1727  D.bt = 0; // diagonal backtrace
1728  if(D.score >= H.score){
1729  H = D;
1730  }
1731  // vertical
1732  V = D = get_bitvec(masks[0], i)? cells[0]->buffer[i] : KBM_CELL_NULL;
1733  {
1734  V.score += score;
1735  V.mat += m->kmat;
1736  //V.gap = 0;
1737  }
1738  if(V.var > 0){
1739  V.score += - aux->par->pvar; // score increases for abs(var) decreased
1740  } else {
1741  V.score += aux->par->pvar;
1742  }
1743  V.var --;
1744  V.bt = 2; // vertical backtrace
1745  if(V.score > H.score){
1746  H = V;
1747  }
1748  if(is_gap){
1749  H.gap ++;
1750  } else {
1751  H.gap = 0;
1752  }
1753  set_bit2vec(dp->bts, dp->bts->size + i, H.bt);
1754  // init new path ID when there is no progenitor
1755  if(H.beg == 0){
1756  H.beg = 1 + i + celoff;
1757  }
1758 #if __DEBUG__
1759  if(KBM_LOG >= KBM_LOG_ALL){
1760  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "KBMLOG%d [x=%d, y=%llu, beg=%llu, score=%d, gap=%d, var=%d, bt=%d]\n", __LINE__, i, dp->last_bidx, (u8i)H.beg, H.score, H.gap, H.var, H.bt);
1761  }
1762 #endif
1763  if(H.score > 0 && H.gap <= aux->par->max_bgap && num_abs(H.var) <= aux->par->max_bvar){
1764  // set cell, move next
1765  one_bitvec(masks[1], i);
1766  cells[1]->buffer[i] = H;
1767  if(is_gap == 0 && H.mat >= aux->par->min_mat) _update_dp_path_kbm(dp, 1 + i + celoff, &H);
1768  i ++;
1769  } else if(D.score > 0){
1770  // move next, may have diagonal hit
1771  zero_bitvec(masks[1], i);
1772  H = KBM_CELL_NULL;
1773  i ++;
1774  } else {
1775  zero_bitvec(masks[1], i);
1776  ni = next_one_bitvec(masks[1], i + 1);
1777  if(i + 1 < ni){
1778  reg_zeros_bitvec(masks[1], i + 1, ni);
1779  D = H = KBM_CELL_NULL;
1780  }
1781  i = ni;
1782  }
1783  }
1784  // prepare next row
1785  //NEXT_ROW:
1786  push_u4v(dp->coffs, dp->cms->size);
1787  zero_bitvec(dp->cmask, dp->cmask->n_bit);
1788  dp->cmask->n_bit += aux->qnbit;
1789  one_bitvec(dp->cmask, dp->cmask->n_bit);
1790  dp->bts->size += aux->qnbin;
1791  dp->last_bidx ++;
1792 }

◆ filter_reads_kbm()

static u8i filter_reads_kbm ( KBM *  kbm,
u8i  retain_size,
int  strategy 
)
inlinestatic
457  {
458  u8i m, b, e, len;
459  if(kbm->reads->size == 0) return 0;
460  if(retain_size == 0 || retain_size >= kbm->rdseqs->size) return kbm->rdseqs->size;
461  if((kbm->flags & 0x2) == 0){
462  if(kbm->par->rd_len_order){
463  sort_array(kbm->reads->buffer, kbm->reads->size, kbm_read_t, num_cmpgt(b.rdlen, a.rdlen));
464  if(strategy == 0){ // longest
465  len = 0;
466  for(e=0;e<kbm->reads->size;e++){
467  len += kbm->reads->buffer[e].rdlen;
468  if(len >= retain_size) break;
469  }
470  kbm->reads->size = e;
471  } else if(strategy == 1){ // median
472  m = kbm->reads->size / 2;
473  len = kbm->reads->buffer[m].rdlen;
474  e = m;
475  for(b=0;b<=m&&len<retain_size;b++){
476  len += kbm->reads->buffer[m - b].rdlen;
477  len += kbm->reads->buffer[m + b].rdlen;
478  }
479  e = b * 2;
480  b = m - b;
481  if(b){
482  remove_array_kbmreadv(kbm->reads, 0, b);
483  }
484  kbm->reads->size = e;
485  } else {
486  return kbm->rdseqs->size;
487  }
488  return len;
489  } else {
490  return kbm->rdseqs->size;
491  }
492  } else {
493  return kbm->rdseqs->size;
494  }
495 }

1009  }
1010  fflush(kmstat);

1012  if(kmstat){

1014  _kcnts = malloc(200 * sizeof(u8i));

1017  }

1019  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "********************** Kmer Frequency **********************\n");

1021  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "********************** 1 - 201 **********************\n");
1022  ktyp = 0;
1023  for(i=0;i<MAX;i++){
1024  ktyp += (i + 1) * kcnts[i];
1025  }

1033  _kcnts[7] = 0.80 * ktyp;
1034  _kcnts[8] = 0.90 * ktyp;
1035  _kcnts[9] = 0.95 * ktyp;
1036  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "Quatiles:\n");
1037  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, " 10%% 20%% 30%% 40%% 50%% 60%% 70%% 80%% 90%% 95%%\n");
1038  off = 0;
1039  for(i=j=0;j<10;j++){
1040  while(off < _kcnts[j] && i < MAX){
1041  off += kcnts[i] * (i + 1);
1042  i ++;
1043  }
1044  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "%6llu", i);
1045  }
1046  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\n");
1047  fprintf(KBM_LOGF,

1050  );
1051  free(_kcnts);
1052  free(txt);
1053  }
1054  // delete low freq kmer from hash
1055  thread_apply_all(midx, midx->task = 2);
1056  // freeze hash to save memory and speed up the query
1057  for(i=0;i<KBM_N_HASH;i++){
1058  if(0){
1059  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "%12llu ", (u8i)kbm->hashs[i]->count); fflush(KBM_LOGF);
1060  if((i % 8) == 7){
1061  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\n"); fflush(KBM_LOGF);
1062  }
1063  }
1064  freeze_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i], 1.0 / 16);
1065  free_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[i]);
1066  kbm->kauxs[i] = init_kbmkauxv(kbm->hashs[i]->count);
1067  kbm->kauxs[i]->size = kbm->hashs[i]->count;
1068  }
1069  print_proc_stat_info(0);
1070  ktot = nrem = Nrem = none = nflt = ktyp = 0;
1071  for(i=0;i+1<MAX;i++){
1072  ktot += kcnts[i];
1073  if(i + 1 < kbm->par->kmin){
1074  none += kcnts[i];
1075  } else {
1076  ktyp += kcnts[i] * (i + 1);
1077  }
1078  }
1079  if(kbm->par->ktop){
1080  off = 0;
1081  for(i=MAX;i>kbm->par->kmin;i--){
1082  off += kcnts[i-1] * i;
1083  if(off >= (ktyp * kbm->par->ktop)) break;
1084  }
1085  if(i > kbm->par->kmax){
1086  kbm->par->kmax = i;
1087  }
1088  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - high frequency kmer depth is set to %d\n", date(), kbm->par->kmax);
1089  }
1090  for(i=kbm->par->kmin? kbm->par->kmin - 1 : 0;i<kbm->par->kmax;i++){
1091  nrem += kcnts[i];
1092  Nrem += kcnts[i] * (i + 1);
1093  }
1094  for(i=kbm->par->kmax;i+1<MAX;i++){
1095  nflt += kcnts[i];
1096  }
1097  off = 0;
1098  thread_apply_all(midx, midx->task = 4);
1099  thread_beg_iter(midx);
1100  cnt = midx->offset;
1101  midx->offset = off;
1102  off += cnt;
1103  midx->task = 5;
1104  thread_wake(midx);
1105  thread_end_iter(midx);
1106  thread_wait_all(midx);
1107  clear_and_encap_kbmbmerv(kbm->seeds, off + 1);
1108  kbm->seeds->size = off;
1109  free_kbmbauxv(kbm->sauxs);
1110  kbm->sauxs = init_kbmbauxv(off + 1);
1111  kbm->sauxs->size = off;
1112  kavg = Nrem / (nrem + 1);
1113  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - Total kmers = %llu\n", date(), ktot);
1114  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - average kmer depth = %d\n", date(), kavg);
1115  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - %llu low frequency kmers (<%d)\n", date(), none, kbm->par->kmin);
1116  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - %llu high frequency kmers (>%d)\n", date(), nflt, kbm->par->kmax);
1117  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - indexing %llu kmers, %llu instances (at most)\n", date(), nrem, Nrem);
1118  thread_apply_all(midx, midx->task = 6);
1119  if(KBM_LOG == 0){ fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\r%llu bins\n", end - beg); fflush(KBM_LOGF); }
1120  thread_apply_all(midx, midx->task = 7);
1121  srem = Srem = 0;
1122  thread_beg_iter(midx);
1123  srem += midx->srem;
1124  Srem += midx->Srem;
1125  thread_end_iter(midx);
1126  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - indexed %llu kmers, %llu instances\n", date(), srem, Srem);
1127  {
1128  n = 0;
1129  for(i=beg;i<end;i++){
1130  if(kbm->bins->buffer[i].degree < kbm->par->min_bin_degree){
1131  kbm->bins->buffer[i].closed = 1;
1132  one_bitvec(kbm->binmarks, i);
1133  n ++;
1134  }
1135  }
1136  index_bitvec(kbm->binmarks);
1137  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - masked %llu bins as closed\n", date(), n);
1138  }
1139  fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "[%s] - sorting\n", date());
1140  thread_apply_all(midx, midx->task = 8);
1141  if(kcnts) free(kcnts);
1142  thread_beg_close(midx);
1143  if(midx->cnts) free(midx->cnts);
1144  thread_end_close(midx);
1145  if(1){

1147  }
1148  print_proc_stat_info(0);
1149 }

2182  if(ref->boff >= ref->bend) break;
2183 #if __DEBUG__

2186  abort();
2187  }
2188 #endif
2189  hidx = ref->bidx / aux->bmcnt;
2190  if(hidx > aux->hptr){
2191  if(hidx - aux->bmoff < aux->nheap){
2192  push_u4v(aux->heaps[hidx - aux->bmoff], idx);
2193  }
2194  break;
2195  }
2196  }
2197  }
2198  {
2199 #ifdef TEST_MODE
2200  if(aux->par->test_mode <= 2){
2201 #endif
2202  if(aux->caches[0]->size * (aux->par->ksize + aux->par->psize) < UInt(aux->par->min_mat)){
2203  aux->caches[0]->size = 0;
2204  } else {
2205  sort_array(aux->caches[0]->buffer, aux->caches[0]->size, kbm_dpe_t, num_cmpgtx(a.bidx, b.bidx, a.poff, b.poff));
2206  }
2207  if(aux->caches[1]->size * (aux->par->ksize + aux->par->psize) < UInt(aux->par->min_mat)){

2211  }

2215 #ifdef TEST_MODE
2216  }
2217 #endif
2218 #ifdef TEST_MODE
2219  if(aux->par->test_mode <= 1){
2220 #endif
2221  for(i=0;i<2;i++){
2222  for(j=0;j<aux->caches[i]->size;j++){

2225  //fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "KBMLOG%d\t%d\t%d\t%c\t%d\t%llu[%d,%d]\t%llu[%d,%d]\n", __LINE__, aux->qidx, ref->poffs[ref->pdir], "+-"[ref->pdir], aux->hptr, ref->bidx, aux->kbm->bins->buffer[ref->bidx].ridx, aux->kbm->bins->buffer[ref->bidx].off * KBM_BIN_SIZE, (u8i)e->bidx, aux->kbm->bins->buffer[e->bidx].ridx, e->poff);
2226  }

2228  push_kmer_match_kbm(aux, i, aux->caches[i]->buffer + j);
2229  }
2230  }
2231  if(aux->hits->size >= aux->par->max_hit) return;
2232 #ifdef TEST_MODE
2233  }
2234 #endif
2235  }
2236  }
2237  aux->hptr ++;
2238  }
2239  if(aux->par->strand_mask & 0x01) push_kmer_match_kbm(aux, 0, NULL);

2264  dst->cgoff = dst_cigars->size;

static void simple_index_kbm ( KBM *  kbm,

u8i  end

1165  // count kmers
1166  {

1178  if(exists){
1179  if(u->tot < KBM_MAX_KCNT) u->tot ++;
1180  } else {
1181  u->mer = f->kmer;
1182  u->tot = 1;
1183  u->flt = 0;
1184  }
1185  }
1186  }
1187  }
1188  }
1189  // delete low freq kmers
1190  if(kbm->par->kmin){

1192  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0]))){
1193  if(u->tot < kbm->par->kmin){
1194  delete_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0], u);
1195  }
1196  }
1197  }
1198  // freeze hash
1199  {

1201  free_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[0]);
1202  kbm->kauxs[0] = init_kbmkauxv(kbm->hashs[0]->count);
1203  kbm->kauxs[0]->size = kbm->hashs[0]->count;
1204  }
1205  // encap seeds
1206  {
1207  off = 0;
1208  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0]);
1209  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0]))){
1210  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[0], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0], u));
1211  x->off = off;
1212  x->cnt = 0;
1213  if(u->tot < kbm->par->kmin){ // Never happens
1214  u->flt = 1;
1215  } else if(kbm->par->kmax && u->tot > kbm->par->kmax){
1216  u->flt = 1;
1217  } else {
1218  off += u->tot;
1219  }
1220  }
1221  clear_and_encap_kbmbmerv(kbm->seeds, off + 1);
1222  kbm->seeds->size = off;
1223  clear_and_encap_kbmbauxv(kbm->sauxs, off + 1);
1224  kbm->sauxs->size = off;
1225  }
1226  // fill seeds

1230  if(bin->closed) continue;
1231  if(((u4i)bin->off + 1) * KBM_BIN_SIZE > kbm->reads->buffer[bin->ridx].rdlen) continue;

1233  split_FIXP_kmers_kbm(kbm->rdseqs, off, KBM_BIN_SIZE, kbm->par->ksize, kbm->par->psize, kbm->par->kmer_mod, kmers);
1234  for(i=0;i<2;i++){

1237  if(f->closed) continue;
1238  u = get_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0], f->kmer);
1239  if(u == NULL || u->flt) continue;
1240  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[0], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0], u));
1241  kbm->bins->buffer[bidx].degree ++;
1242  if(x->cnt < u->tot){
1243  if(x->cnt && getval_bidx(kbm, x->off + x->cnt - 1) == bidx && kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt - 1].dir == i){
1244  // repeated kmer within one bin
1245  } else {
1246  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].bidx = bidx & MAX_U4;
1247  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].bidx = bidx >> 32;
1248  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].dir = i;
1249  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].koff = f->off >> 1;
1250  x->cnt ++;
1251  }
1252  }
1253  }
1254  }
1255  }
1256  }
1257  // sort seeds within a kmer
1258  {
1259  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0]);
1260  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0]))){
1261  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[0], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[0], u));
1262  clear_tmpbmerv(bms);
1263  for(j=0;j<x->cnt;j++){
1264  push_tmpbmerv(bms, (kbm_tmp_bmer_t){getval_bidx(kbm, x->off + j), kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + j]});
1265  }
1266  sort_array(bms->buffer, bms->size, kbm_tmp_bmer_t, num_cmpgt(a.bidx, b.bidx));
1267  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + 0].bidx = bms->buffer[0].bidx & MAX_U4;
1268  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + 0].bidx = bms->buffer[0].bidx >> 32;
1269  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + 0] = bms->buffer[0].aux;
1270  len = 1;
1271  for(j=1;j<x->cnt;j++){
1272  if(bms->buffer[j].bidx < bms->buffer[j - 1].bidx){
1273  continue;
1274  }
1275  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + len].bidx = bms->buffer[j].bidx & MAX_U4;
1276  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + len].bidx = bms->buffer[0].bidx >> 32;
1277  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + len] = bms->buffer[j].aux;
1278  len ++;
1279  }
1280  x->cnt = len;
1281  }
1282  }
1283  free_kmeroffv(kmers[0]);
1284  free_kmeroffv(kmers[1]);

static void split_FIXP_kmers_kbm ( BaseBank *  rdseqs,
u8i  offset,
u4i  length,
u1i  ksize,
u1i  psize,
u4i  kmod,

536  {
537  kmer_off_t *kp;
538  u8i kmer, krev, hv, npz, kmask, p, pmask;
539  u4i ki, npl;
540  int i, j;
541  u1i c, b, kshift, pshift, kpshf;
542  clear_kmeroffv(rs[0]);
543  clear_kmeroffv(rs[1]);
544  kshift = (ksize - 1) << 1;
545  kmask = (1LLU << (ksize << 1)) - 1LLU;
546  pshift = (psize - 1) << 1;
547  pmask = (1LLU << (psize << 1)) - 1LLU;
548  kpshf = psize << 1;
549  if(ksize){
550  // scan F-part of kmers
551  kmer = krev = 0;
552  for(i=0;i+1<ksize;i++){
553  c = bits2bit(rdseqs->bits, offset + i);
554  kmer = (kmer << 2) | c;
555  krev = (krev >> 2) | (((u8i)((~c) & 0x3)) << kshift);
556  }
557  for(;i<(int)length;i++){
558  c = bits2bit(rdseqs->bits, offset + i);
559  kmer = ((kmer << 2) | c) & kmask;
560  krev = (krev >> 2) | (((u8i)((~c) & 0x3)) << kshift);
561  if(kmer < krev){
562  push_kmeroffv(rs[0], (kmer_off_t){kmer, i - (ksize - 1), 0, 0, 1});
563  } else if(krev < kmer){
564  push_kmeroffv(rs[1], (kmer_off_t){krev, i - (ksize - 1), 0, 1, 1});
565  }
566  }
567  if(psize){
568  // scan P-part of forward kmers
569  assert(rs[0]->n_head > 0);
570  memset(rs[0]->buffer - 1, 0, sizeof(kmer_off_t)); // rs[0]->n_head > 0
571  rs[0]->buffer[-1].off = length;
572  npz = 0;
573  npl = 0;
574  kp = rs[0]->buffer + rs[0]->size - 1;
575  b = 4;
576  for(i=length-1;i>=0;i--){
577  if(kp->off + (ksize - 1) == (u4i)i){
578  if(npl >= psize){
579  p = npz & pmask;
580  kp->closed = 0;
581  kp->kmer = (kp->kmer << kpshf) | p;
582  }
583  kp --;
584  }
585  c = bits2revbit(rdseqs->bits, offset + i);
586  if(c == b){
587  } else {
588  npz = (npz << 2) | c;
589  npl ++;
590  b = c;
591  }
592  }
593  // scan P-part of reverse kmers
594  encap_kmeroffv(rs[1], 1); memset(rs[1]->buffer + rs[1]->size, 0xFF, sizeof(kmer_off_t));
595  npz = 0;
596  npl = 0;
597  kp = rs[1]->buffer;
598  b = 4;
599  for(i=0;i<(int)length;i++){
600  if(kp->off == (u4i)(i)){
601  if(npl >= psize){
602  p = npz & pmask;
603  kp->closed = 0;
604  kp->kmer = (kp->kmer << kpshf) | p;
605  kp->off = kp->off - psize;
606  }
607  kp ++;
608  }
609  c = bits2bit(rdseqs->bits, offset + i);
610  if(c == b){
611  } else {
612  npz = (npz << 2) | c;
613  npl ++;
614  b = c;
615  }
616  }
617  } else {
618  for(i=0;(u4i)i<rs[0]->size;i++) rs[0]->buffer[i].closed = 0;
619  for(i=0;(u4i)i<rs[1]->size;i++) rs[1]->buffer[i].closed = 0;
620  }
621  } else if(psize){
622  kmer = krev = 0;
623  b = 4;
624  for(i=j=0;i<(int)length;i++){
625  c = bits2bit(rdseqs->bits, offset + i);
626  if(b == c) continue;
627  b = c;
628  kmer = ((kmer << 2) | c) & pmask;
629  krev = (krev >> 2) | (((u8i)((~c) & 0x3)) << pshift);
630  j ++;
631  if(j < psize) continue;
632  if(kmer < krev){
633  push_kmeroffv(rs[0], (kmer_off_t){kmer, i - (psize - 1), 0, 0, 0});
634  } else if(krev < kmer){
635  push_kmeroffv(rs[1], (kmer_off_t){krev, i - (psize - 1), 0, 1, 0});
636  }
637  }
638  }
639  for(b=0;b<2;b++){
640  for(i=0;(u4i)i<rs[b]->size;i++){
641  if(rs[b]->buffer[i].closed) continue;
642  hv = kbm_kmer_smear(rs[b]->buffer[i].kmer);
643  ki = hv % kmod;
644  if(ki >= KBM_N_HASH) rs[b]->buffer[i].closed = 1;
645  rs[b]->buffer[i].kidx = ki;
646  }
647  }
648 }

716  {
717  // counting kmers
718  for(i=0;i<KBM_N_HASH;i++) clear_kbmmidxv(kidxs[i]);
719  for(bidx=midx->beg+tidx;bidx<midx->end;bidx+=ncpu){
720  if(KBM_LOG == 0 && tidx == 0 && ((bidx - midx->beg) % 100000) == 0){ fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\r%u", bidx - midx->beg); fflush(KBM_LOGF); }
721  bin = ref_kbmbinv(kbm->bins, bidx);
722  if(bin->closed) continue;
723  if(((u4i)bin->off + 1) * KBM_BIN_SIZE > kbm->reads->buffer[bin->ridx].rdlen) continue;
724  off = kbm->reads->buffer[bin->ridx].rdoff + bin->off * KBM_BIN_SIZE;
725  len = KBM_BIN_SIZE;
726  split_FIXP_kmers_kbm(kbm->rdseqs, off, len, kbm->par->ksize, kbm->par->psize, kbm->par->kmer_mod, kmers);
727  for(i=0;i<2;i++){

730  if(f->closed) continue;
731  mx = next_ref_kbmmidxv(kidxs[f->kidx]);
732  mx->mer = f->kmer;
733  mx->kidx = f->kidx;
734  mx->bidx = bidx;
735  mx->dir = i;
736  mx->koff = f->off;
737  if(kidxs[f->kidx]->size >= 64){
738  kidx = f->kidx;
739  // lock hashs[kidx]
740  pthread_mutex_lock(midx->locks + kidx);
741  // hash adding
742  for(k=0;k<kidxs[kidx]->size;k++){
743  mx = ref_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx], k);
744  u = prepare_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[kidx], mx->mer, &exists);
745  if(exists){
746  if(u->tot < KBM_MAX_KCNT) u->tot ++;
747  } else {
748  u->mer = mx->mer;
749  u->tot = 1;
750  u->flt = 0;
751  }
752  }
753  // free hashs[f->kidx]
754  pthread_mutex_unlock(midx->locks + kidx);
755  clear_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx]);
756  }
757  }
758  }
759  }
760  for(kidx=0;kidx<KBM_N_HASH;kidx++){
761  if(kidxs[kidx]->size){
762  // lock hashs[kidx]
763  pthread_mutex_lock(midx->locks + kidx);
764  // hash adding
765  for(k=0;k<kidxs[kidx]->size;k++){
766  mx = ref_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx], k);
767  u = prepare_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[kidx], mx->mer, &exists);
768  if(exists){
769  if(u->tot < KBM_MAX_KCNT) u->tot ++;
770  } else {
771  u->mer = mx->mer;
772  u->tot = 1;
773  u->flt = 0;
774  }
775  }
776  // free hashs[f->kidx]
777  pthread_mutex_unlock(midx->locks + kidx);
778  clear_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx]);
779  }
780  }
781 } else if(midx->task == 2){
782  // delete low freq kmers
783  for(i=tidx;i<KBM_N_HASH;i+=ncpu){
784  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]);
785  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]))){
786  if(u->tot < kbm->par->kmin){
787  delete_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i], u);
788  }
789  }
790  }
791 } else if(midx->task == 3){
792  // stat kmer counts
793  memset(midx->cnts, 0, midx->n_cnt * sizeof(u8i));
794  for(i=tidx;i<KBM_N_HASH;i+=ncpu){
795  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]);
796  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]))){
797  midx->cnts[num_min(midx->n_cnt, u->tot) - 1] ++;
798  }
799  }
800 } else if(midx->task == 4){
801  // stat counts
802  midx->offset = 0;
803  for(i=tidx;i<KBM_N_HASH;i+=ncpu){
804  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]);
805  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]))){
806  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[i], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i], u));
807  x->off = midx->offset;
808  x->cnt = 0;
809  midx->ktot += u->tot;
810  if(u->tot < kbm->par->kmin){
811  u->flt = 1;
812  } else if(u->tot > kbm->par->kmax){
813  u->flt = 1;
814  } else {
815  midx->offset += u->tot;
816  }
817  }
818  }
819 } else if(midx->task == 5){
820  // revise offset
821  for(i=tidx;i<KBM_N_HASH;i+=ncpu){
822  for(off=0;off<kbm->kauxs[i]->size;off++) kbm->kauxs[i]->buffer[off].off += midx->offset;
823  }
824 } else if(midx->task == 6){
825  // fill seeds
826  for(i=0;i<KBM_N_HASH;i++) clear_kbmmidxv(kidxs[i]);
827  u4v *chgs;
828  chgs = init_u4v(KBM_BSIZE);
829  for(bidx=midx->beg+tidx;bidx<midx->end;bidx+=ncpu){
830  if(KBM_LOG == 0 && tidx == 0 && ((bidx - midx->beg) % 100000) == 0){ fprintf(KBM_LOGF, "\r%u", bidx - midx->beg); fflush(KBM_LOGF); }
831  bin = ref_kbmbinv(kbm->bins, bidx);
832  if(bin->closed) continue;
833  bin->degree = 0;
834  if(((u4i)bin->off + 1) * KBM_BIN_SIZE > kbm->reads->buffer[bin->ridx].rdlen) continue;
835  off = kbm->reads->buffer[bin->ridx].rdoff + bin->off * KBM_BIN_SIZE;
836  len = KBM_BIN_SIZE;
837  split_FIXP_kmers_kbm(kbm->rdseqs, off, len, kbm->par->ksize, kbm->par->psize, kbm->par->kmer_mod, kmers);
838  clear_u4v(chgs);
839  for(i=0;i<2;i++){
840  for(j=0;j<kmers[i]->size;j++){
841  f = ref_kmeroffv(kmers[i], j);
842  if(f->closed) continue;
843  mx = next_ref_kbmmidxv(kidxs[f->kidx]);
844  mx->mer = f->kmer;
845  mx->kidx = f->kidx;
846  mx->bidx = bidx;
847  mx->dir = i;
848  mx->koff = f->off;
849  if(kidxs[f->kidx]->size == 64){
850  push_u4v(chgs, f->kidx);
851  }
852  }
853  }
854  for(i=0;i<chgs->size;i++){
855  kidx = chgs->buffer[i];
856  if(kidxs[kidx]->size == 0) continue;
857  pthread_mutex_lock(midx->locks + kidx);
858  for(k=0;k<kidxs[kidx]->size;k++){
859  mx = ref_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx], k);
860  u = get_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[kidx], mx->mer);
861  if(u && u->flt == 0){
862  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[kidx], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[kidx], u));
863  kbm->bins->buffer[mx->bidx].degree ++;
864  if(x->cnt < u->tot){
865  if(x->cnt && getval_bidx(kbm, x->off + x->cnt - 1) == mx->bidx && kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt - 1].dir == mx->dir){
866  // repeated kmer within one bin
867  } else {
868  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].bidx = mx->bidx & MAX_U4;
869  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].bidx = mx->bidx >> 32;
870  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].dir = mx->dir;
871  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].koff = mx->koff >> 1;
872  x->cnt ++;
873  }
874  }
875  }
876  }
877  pthread_mutex_unlock(midx->locks + kidx);
878  clear_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx]);
879  }
880  }
881  for(kidx=0;kidx<KBM_N_HASH;kidx++){
882  if(kidxs[kidx]->size){
883  // lock hashs[kidx]
884  pthread_mutex_lock(midx->locks + kidx);
885  // hash adding
886  for(k=0;k<kidxs[kidx]->size;k++){
887  mx = ref_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx], k);
888  u = get_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[kidx], mx->mer);
889  if(u && u->flt == 0){
890  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[kidx], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[kidx], u));
891  kbm->bins->buffer[mx->bidx].degree ++;
892  if(x->cnt < u->tot){
893  if(x->cnt && getval_bidx(kbm, x->off + x->cnt - 1) == mx->bidx && kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt - 1].dir == mx->dir){
894  // repeated kmer within one bin
895  } else {
896  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].bidx = mx->bidx & MAX_U4;
897  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].bidx = mx->bidx >> 32;
898  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].dir = mx->dir;
899  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + x->cnt].koff = mx->koff >> 1;
900  x->cnt ++;
901  }
902  }
903  }
904  }
905  // free hashs[f->kidx]
906  pthread_mutex_unlock(midx->locks + kidx);
907  clear_kbmmidxv(kidxs[kidx]);
908  }
909  }
910  free_u4v(chgs);
911 } else if(midx->task == 7){
912  // count added kmers
913  midx->srem = midx->Srem = 0;
914  for(i=tidx;i<KBM_N_HASH;i+=ncpu){
915  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]);
916  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]))){
917  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[i], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i], u));
918  if(x->cnt){
919  midx->srem ++;
920  midx->Srem += x->cnt;
921  }
922  }
923  }
924 } else if(midx->task == 8){
925  // sort seeds within a kmer
926  for(i=tidx;i<KBM_N_HASH;i+=ncpu){
927  reset_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]);
928  while((u = ref_iter_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i]))){
929  x = ref_kbmkauxv(kbm->kauxs[i], offset_kbmhash(kbm->hashs[i], u));
930  if(x->cnt < 2) continue;
931  clear_tmpbmerv(bms);
932  for(j=0;j<x->cnt;j++){
933  push_tmpbmerv(bms, (kbm_tmp_bmer_t){getval_bidx(kbm, x->off + j), kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + j]});
934  }
935  sort_array(bms->buffer, bms->size, kbm_tmp_bmer_t, num_cmpgt(a.bidx, b.bidx));
936  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + 0].bidx = bms->buffer[0].bidx & MAX_U4;
937  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + 0].bidx = bms->buffer[0].bidx >> 32;
938  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + 0] = bms->buffer[0].aux;
939  len = 1;
940  for(j=1;j<x->cnt;j++){
941  if(bms->buffer[j].bidx < bms->buffer[j - 1].bidx){
942  continue;
943  }
944  kbm->seeds->buffer[x->off + len].bidx = bms->buffer[j].bidx & MAX_U4;
945  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + len].bidx = bms->buffer[0].bidx >> 32;
946  kbm->sauxs->buffer[x->off + len] = bms->buffer[j].aux;
947  len ++;
948  }
949  x->cnt = len;
950  }
951  }
952 }
953 thread_end_loop(midx);
954 free_kmeroffv(kmers[0]);
955 free_kmeroffv(kmers[1]);
956 for(i=0;i<KBM_N_HASH;i++) free_kbmmidxv(kidxs[i]);
957 free(kidxs);
958 free_tmpbmerv(bms);
959 thread_end_func(midx);
